📊 Spatiotemporal Crime Prediction (Time-Series Analysis)

This module predicts future crime trends based on historical data using **time-series analysis**. By analyzing the relationship between **crime occurrences, time, and location**, the system provides insights into crime patterns and potential hotspots.

 🚀 Features
- **Predicts crime trends** using historical data.
- **Analyzes spatial and temporal factors** affecting crime occurrences.
- **Generates time-series visualizations** for trend analysis.
- **Uses machine learning models** to enhance prediction accuracy.
- **Displays results in graph format** for easy interpretation.

 🛠️ Technologies Used
- **Programming Language:** Python
- **Libraries:** Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn, Matplotlib, Seaborn, Statsmodels
- **Database:** MySQL Workbench (crime data storage)
- **Visualization:** Matplotlib & Seaborn for trend analysis

📌 Installation

### 🔹 Clone the Repository
```sh
git clone https://github.com/your-username/crime-analysis.git
cd crime-analysis/spatiotemporal-crime-prediction
